item.title: Once More, With Feeling
item.author: Tim Stullich
item.description: I have recently encountered a common problem I am sure lots of programmers have faced before - discovering their graveyard of unfinished side projects. In my particular case, I was scrolling through my Github profile, taking stock of all of the repositories that I have not committed code to in over a year, and the total came out to be a staggering 40 repositories. To me, this is not a great stat, considering I have been actively committing to just 3 repositories in the last year.
